# Orchestrator project rules

## Secrets

- Never commit `.env` or real `CURSOR_API_KEY` values.
- Keep real keys only in `.env`. `.env.example` must stay a placeholder.
- Do not print full API keys in logs, README, commits, or PR text.

## Architecture

- Parallelism = multiple `Agent.create` calls. Never concurrent `send` on one agent.
- Default runtime is local; always pass `local: { cwd }` explicitly.
- Always dispose agents (`finally` or `Symbol.asyncDispose`).
- Loop mode must keep hard stops: max steps, max minutes, and Ctrl+C abort.
- Distinguish startup errors (exit 1) from run failures (exit 2).

## Scope

- Core modes: `once` / `parallel` / `loop` CLI, plus localhost-only UI (`npm run ui`).
- Do not add auto-PR-to-existing-repos or cloud-first ops unless the user asks.
- Keep the UI bound to 127.0.0.1; never expose API keys to the browser.
- Do not design empty-repo spam; future "create repos" work must ship small complete demos.

## Windows

- Prefer `npm.cmd` in PowerShell when `npm.ps1` is blocked by execution policy.

## Docs sync

- When changing CLI flags or safety behavior, update `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `SECURITY.md` if needed.
